# Environment Template for Stellar Team Payout Request

## Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your values

## Stellar Network Configuration

# Network: 'testnet' or 'public' (use testnet for development)
VITE_STELLAR_NETWORK=testnet

# Stellar Horizon server URL
# Testnet: https://horizon-testnet.stellar.org
# Public: https://horizon.stellar.org
VITE_STELLAR_SERVER_URL=https://horizon-testnet.stellar.org

# Network passphrase for transaction signing
# Testnet: Test SDF Network ; September 2015
# Public: Public Global Stellar Network ; September 2015
VITE_STELLAR_NETWORK_PASSPHRASE=Test SDF Network ; September 2015

## Test Keypair (TESTNET ONLY - Never use in production!)

# Stellar secret key for testing (testnet only)
# Generate at: https://stellar.expert/account-creator/testnet
# Or get test account with XLM from: https://developers.stellar.org/docs/tutorials/create-account
# DO NOT commit this file with real secret keys!
VITE_TEST_KEYPAIR_SECRET=

## Optional: Pre-configured destination account for testing

# Test destination account (public key) for testing payments
# Leave empty to enter at runtime
VITE_TEST_DESTINATION_ACCOUNT=

## Development Options

# Enable debug logging (comma-separated patterns)
# DEBUG=stealth:payout:*,stealth:stellar:*
DEBUG=

# Payout request timeout in milliseconds (default: 30000)
VITE_PAYOUT_TIMEOUT_MS=30000

# Maximum retry attempts for failed payouts (default: 3)
VITE_PAYOUT_MAX_RETRIES=3

## Notes

# - All values starting with VITE_ are available in frontend code
# - Do not expose secret keys in production
# - Use secure key management (AWS KMS, HashiCorp Vault, etc.) for production
# - Test values should use testnet keys and accounts only
# - Update VITE_TEST_KEYPAIR_SECRET from https://developers.stellar.org/ after funding
